about.description:
pythonocc is a python package whose purpose is
to provide 3D modeling features. It is intended
to CAD/PDM/PLM and BIM related development.

name: pythonocc-core
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "7.7.2" %}

package:
  name: pythonocc-core
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/tpaviot/pythonocc-core/archive/{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 0f6473be2800a64222ef86a3de70e3beaa2320a3839ebde1b4f6e845a369c0d9

build:
  number: 0

requirements:
  build:
    - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - numpy                                  # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}
    - {{ cdt('mesa-libgl-devel') }}      # [linux]
    - {{ cdt('libxi-devel') }}           # [linux]
    - ninja
    - cmake
    - swig 4.1.1
  host:
    - python
    - occt {{ version }}
    - numpy
  run:
    - python
    - occt
    - six
    - {{ pin_compatible("numpy") }}
    - svgwrite
  run_constrained:
    - occt {{ version }}

test:
  source_files:
    - test
  imports:
    - OCC
    - OCC.Core.BRepPrimAPI
  requires:
    - pyqt >=5

about:
  home: http://www.pythonocc.org/
  license: LGPL-3.0
  license_family: LGPL
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: python bindings for opencascade (occt)
  description: |
    pythonocc is a python package whose purpose is 
    to provide 3D modeling features. It is intended 
    to CAD/PDM/PLM and BIM related development.
  dev_url: https://github.com/tpaviot/pythonocc-core

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - looooo
